// =====================================================================
// DESIGN NOTES
// =====================================================================
//
// Uniqueness: NOT enforced. A crew member can have multiple timecard
// entries for the same project on the same date. Covers split-day work
// (e.g., location hours + office hours same day). UI should group by
// date in display but schema allows multiple rows.
//
// Reopen reason: lightweight single field. If timecard later becomes a
// threadable entity (15th type), this field becomes vestigial but is
// harmless. Do not remove without a migration plan.
//
// onDelete semantics:
//   - Project deleted → cascade timecards (kill project, kill its data)
//   - Crew member (ProjectMember) deleted → RESTRICT (can't delete if
//     timecards exist; requires archiving pattern or explicit cleanup)
//   - Approver/Reopener deleted → SetNull (preserve financial record,
//     lose identity attribution)


